1�You do not have enough gil.
1�Prishe...I still do not know if I can believe what you have just told me.
1�Have the Gates of Paradise truly begun to open...?
1�Yes, where could they have run off to?
1�Do you think they could have set off for Cape Riverne? But why...?
1�...?Something is amiss, Prishe...
1�Granpere...
1� , I am pleased to see you have returned.
1�I, myself, have trouble coming to terms with what I heard.The Keeper of the Apocalypse...The pact...
1�When the keeper is born, the children of Altana must die...
1�Why would Bahamut wish such a terrible fate upon us? What caused him to despise us this much?
1�You knew...!
1�I asked ?[him/her] to give it to Prishe to help her. I wanted to save her...
1�Hm? Secret boxes...?
1�Yes, you were changed by that accident long ago, but you are still Prishe!
1�That... That is...
1�  and Sir Tenzen must return to the Northlands.
1�And they will need the amulet you are currently borrowing...
1�The will of Promathia calls the keeper...?
1�Granpere! It is unfair to blame Prishe for all of Tavnazia's misfortunes!
1�It is because Prishe's heart is pure--that is why she was not controlled by the evil after touching the statue of Promathia...
1�She only did such a foolish thing to save our nation! Why can't you understand this!?
1�Granpere!Have you forgotten what Cardinal Mildaurion told us?
1�She told us Prishe may have been born the abhorrent one, but she was reborn through the power of Altana.
1�Who could have told you such things...!?
1�Louverance...I recall hearing that name once before...when I visited San d'Oria...
1�Granpere!
1�Prishe... But...!
1�Granpere, you know as well as I do...
1�There is nothing abhorrent about Prishe...
1�And I can no longer ignore the problems that loom before us. Goodbye, Granpere.
1�I have never seen Granpere so excited.He plans to hire adventurers to exterminate all the fiends, and then sow fields in Lufaise and Misareaux.
1�He also intends to restore the shepherd villages on Cape Riverne, although a great deal of the land yet floats high above the sea in that unnatural way...
1�No longer shall our homes be overrun by monsters.
1�We need you to focus on becoming the leader of the Tavnazian Cathedral.
1�Prishe...!
1�And yet you have stood by us through it all.We are truly grateful.
1�And should the opportunity arise, we would greatly appreciate any further assistance you could provide for the Marquisate.
1�However...I understand that as an adventurer, there is still much in the world you wish to experience.
1�If you ever feel the need to rest your wings, we will always welcome you here in Tavnazia.
1�I hope we may meet again,  .
1�Prishe!This is hardly the time to be engaging in idle chatter! Your studies await!
1�That girl...
1�It's wonderful to see you in such high spirits,  . I always knew in my heart of hearts that we would meet again.
1�As you can see, Prishe is as lively as she's ever been.
1�Who knows where she, I, and all of Tavnazia would be without you,  .Please return to visit us again sometime. Preferably after Prishe's lessons are finished.
1�So you finally decided to show up. I've heard all about you from Justinius. Sounds like you've had a hell of a time since you got here.
1�But I'm not one to pry. To put it in other words, I just don't give a damn.
1�But there is one thing that's been bugging me. Where did you get your hands on this amulet?
1�A white-haired boy? That's strange... Are you sure you don't mean a tall blonde chick?
1�Anyway, I'm not a thief, so you can have this back.
1�What did you...
1�What's wrong, Despachiaire? You never come to my quarters.
1�I'm the ??abhorrent one.?? I thought if you talked to me you'd be punished by the goddess.
1�Whatever.Anyway, what is it that you want?
1�That's exactly what happened! I'd never seen anything like it. If that monster decided to attack us, there wouldn't be a trace of this place left.
1�Al'Taieu?
1�But if the dragon I saw was the same as in the painting, then that would mean the beast was...Bahamut!?
1�I've got to check this out!You, find Ulmia and bring her back here quick!
1�Yeah, I saw it. Left by another dragon, right? How many of those things are there, anyway?
1�How the hell should I know? That's why we're going to ask Bahamut, right?
1�Hm...You'd think at least those troublemaking Tarutaru would want to come. Where are they, anyway?
1�Where did you say you saw him?
1�Huh!? Why, those conniving...!
1�There's only one reason. They smell an adventure!C'mon! We've got no time to lose!
1�Phew...It's good to be back home!
1�What's with the long faces? I'm back!Break out the brew and grub!
1�What's going on here, Justinius? Did anything happen while I was gone?
1�Thanks for coming to visit. I've been so bored here, all alone in my room.
1�You didn't realize? Does it look like I had any idea either?
1�I was just trying to protect our criminal buddy,  . Who would have thought I'd be the one who got caught?
1�Oh well. I'm sorry that I got you guys all worried over me.
1�When Miss Mildaurion became boss, she would often let me out of the church so I could roam around the town freely. It was pretty fun...
1�During the Great War, I was able to help a lot of people, and before long everyone had started to forget why they feared me.
1�But now look! They're never going to let me out of here again! Damn!
1�Come on, topknot boy. Don't you get it? , you understand what's going on, right?
1�That's right. Take a look at me. I haven't aged a day since that accident!
1�Huh? Have you been paying attention at all the past few days?
1�Look at me. I haven't aged a single day since my accident.
1�The real reason I was locked up in the cathedral for so long was because I got too close to a certain object hidden deep below the church...
1�I was about to touch it, and BOOM! There was this bright light, and I was left like this.
1�If I were a Tarutaru, no one would have ever noticed, but I'm Elvaan. After a couple of years, people started to wonder why I wasn't getting any bigger.
1�Die? Hell if I know. And I'm not throwing myself off any cliffs to find out.
1�But you know, since the accident, no monster has come near me. I guess you could say that's pretty close to immortality.
1�Whoa, wait a minute!How do we know that you really came here to see Bahamut?
1�You'd better not be thinking of auctioning me off to your leaders, 'cause I'm not for sale!
1�What!?You've already met Bahamut!?
1�Unbelievable!Why the hell didn't anybody tell me what was going on?Tenzen! If you want to apologize for something, start by apologizing for not taking me with you guys!
1�While I'm sitting here twiddling my thumbs, the whole world's turning upside down, and you're the ones having all the fun!
1�Well, now it's time for Prishe to get a piece of the action. I'll find that overgrown steam lizard and give him a piece of my mind!
1�Fine by me...But why do we have to go back to the Northlands? That place is freezing!
1�The will of Promathia?
1�(So, what you really want is to ask this boy about what Promathia's thinking, right?)
1�(Well, instead of wasting your time chasing after some crazy boy, why don't we go and ask Promathia ourselves?)
1�(I know where we can find him.)

1�(Heh heh. On the Misareaux Coast, there's a cave leading to the Sacrarium. Head there and you'll see what I'm talking about. But don't forget your preparations before you go...unless you really want to meet Promathia--just not in this world!)
1�Who the hell are you!?
1�Miss Mildaurion! You've got to be kidding!?
1�Ulmia, don't worry.I was beginning to think that it's about time everybody learned the truth.
1�I've gotta do something, or people will continue to doubt and hate me.
1�Hey, Louverance!As much as I'd like to take up your offer of a free cruise to the Kingdom, I'm gonna have to pass. I gotta go to the Northlands with these guys before I can do anything else.
1�Like they say, a promise is a promise.
1�It's all over.The town has finally found peace again.
1�I haven't seen Miss Mildaurion for a while, but she did send a messenger.Looks like Jeuno is willing to continue supporting the safehold.
1�Unlike Nag'molada's flimsy promises, with this arrangement we'll be able to govern ourselves.
1�Sure, the dragons are gone, but we've still got a lot of work to do.
1�And don't you give me that sympathetic look.You adventurers will have plenty of opportunities to pitch in.
1�Wha--!?I'm off to get my workout!
1�Later!
1�I'll tell you where I'll put my hooves if you're gonna keep secrets from me!
1�I knew you could do it,  ! No one can come close to matching your awesomeness!
1�I see you're at it again,  .We all know how powerful you are, so how about throwing the patrol a bone every once in a while? We're dying for some good press!
1�Justinius has told me all about your exploits.You're always there for Tavnazia when it needs you,  . Thanks.
1�Although, I guess it should only be a matter of time before we get our due, what with all the Voidwalkers crawling around Tavnazia lately.
1�Just you wait! We'll cut down so many of those mystical invaders that...well, there won't be any left for you!
1�But Voidwalkers tend to reappear like maggots on meat, right?
1�Maybe this's the Tavnazian Patrol's chance to get some good press of our own!
1�Yikes!For crying out loud, Ulmia, you've become more of a curmudgeon than Despachiaire!
1�Ulmia!
1�Anyway,  , I'll see you later!
1�I guess I've been corralled...See you around.
1�Yeah! A fight to the death!
1�You're one of those bad, bad rogues!
1�It's time for you to be punished!
1�You wouldn't do that, Justinius!
1�I know! We can use these two as bait for the minotaur!
1�Yeah! Prove that you're innocent!
1�Hey you! We know who you really are! Tell us who you really are!
1�You're one of those evil black mages!
1�You couldn't do that, Justinius!
1�Yeah! They'll surely be sentenced to death once Prishe gets back, right?
1�The soldiers have left the Sacrarium! They're headin' up and movin' out!
1�But that amulet is Prishe's! I bet that funny-looking adventurer stole it from her!
1�You're one of those red lion traitors!
1�If they're gonna die anyway, why not put them to good use!?
1�They've finished packing their secret boxes! They've got what they want and now they're gone!
1�You...I thought you had perished!
1�Amulet!?So that explains...
1�So this is what remains of the mighty nation of Tavnazia... Its people alone behind these walls, struggling to stay alive for the past twenty years...
1�The Tavnazian Cathedral...
1�No...Why not let us attempt to rid your city of its pest problem?
1�Adventurers travel the world in search of new challenges. If defeating this minotaur can help us gain the trust of your people, we would be fools not to try.
1�?[He/She] is tired from recent ordeals and ?[his/her] mind is still clouded. However, you need not fear. ?[He/She] will defeat the minotaur. I guarantee it.
1�Promathia...Simply speaking his name brings damnation.
1�As has the Dawn Goddess, Altana, the Twilight God has existed since the beginning of time.

1�However, unlike the kind and giving Altana, Promathia is known as the Lord of Chaos. It is said that his curse, unleashed on mankind for the sin of opening the Gates of Paradise, dooms us to an eternity of strife.
1�The only way for us to be saved from this horrendous curse is to forget it, and that is why the name Promathia cannot be seen nor heard anywhere across Vana'diel.
1�This is one of the reasons why your people in the East know nothing of Promathia. Without a name, how can anything exist?
1�Your people are probably better off not knowing the tainted history this world has locked up in its past.
1�Truths we must not know.Truths we should not know.And truths we are forced to face...
1�We must be careful with these truths, for if we are not, they could bring tragedy.
1�For example, Bahamut's warning.We knew all along that Bahamut would one day appear and attempt to destroy us...

1�Your imprudent meddling has interfered with our plans and prevented us from accomplishing our mission! Do you truly wish to see the bodies of your fallen brothers lie sprawled across the barren plains of a dead world?
1�Tenzen.Stopping the Emptiness from spreading--is this not the wish of both our peoples?
1�Seeking out Bahamut on your own, without any set reason, ultimately disrupting our plans... Why, this sounds like nothing more than treason!
1�Fine.However, from now on I request that you leave all matters dealing with the Wyrmking to the Duchy.
1�Differences in thinking can cause different reactions from different races. However, we in Jeuno care naught of differences. Our wish is only to save all the children of Vana'diel.
1�Everything is in motion. However, as for the details, I, myself, know little.
1�My assignment has nothing to do with Bahamut. My mission is to stop that boy.
1�Hm...? , where is your amulet?
1�What!? Gave it away!?You imbecile! How could you just let go of such an important item!?
1�Prishe?
1�Ah... I see.If the amulet is still here, then...
1� .Retrieve the amulet from the girl and bring it to the resting place of the fourth crystal in the Northlands.
1�The crystal is located deep below Castle Zvahl, and it can only be reached by traversing the ruins of Pso'Xja.
1� .Come to the far western entrance of Pso'Xja, but not without the amulet. I will be waiting for you there.
1�Welcome to our humble city, though there is little left of it...I heard from Justinius the details of your predicament.
1�He mentioned that you were from the mainland.
1�Tell me, what is the situation beyond the churning seas?
1�No one has the time to wonder about the fates of their lost brothers...
1�For twenty years, we have dug and carved our way up from a narrow storageway below the Tavnazian Cathedral...
1�As an adventurer, I am sure you have heard tales of the Pearl of Zafmlug--the renowned Tavnazian Marquisate.
1�Her wide harbors would welcome ships from all corners of Vana'diel, carrying never-before-seen goods and treasures.
1�A mecca of trade. A place where dreams of wealth and success could become reality... It was the golden age of Tavnazia.

1�But it all came to a close twenty years ago. The beastman hordes concentrated their attack on our fair nation, and when they were through, there was nothing left but a wasteland uninhabitable by even the foulest of creatures.
1�We, too, should have met the same fate as the Marquisate...
1�Late in our escape from the peninsula, we made for the cathedral, where we awaited our deaths at the hands of the Orcs.
1�She tended to our wounded bodies and spirits, and informed us how to escape.
1�She opened the gates to the lower parts of the cathedral, and told us to follow the delivery tunnels to the city.
1�We did as we were told, and it was not long before we arrived at the subterranean harbor deep beneath this place.
1�However, by the time we had arrived, the boats had already gone, and a terrible explosion had destroyed the landbridge to Quon... We were trapped...
1�But even with our backs against the wall of despair, the courage and faith we had received from the cardinal remained in our hearts.
1�For the past twenty years we have survived on the belief that Altana will save us. It is that belief that has helped us to come together and rebuild our nation.
1�However, we still struggle to provide for even ourselves. I am sorry we cannot offer you any more than a warm welcome.
1�But please, feel free to utilize any of our facilities.
1�I pray that the powers that led you to Tavnazia become a blessing for both our peoples.
1�Prishe, do you have a moment?
1�I heard of what transpired on Cape Riverne--that a great dragon appeared.
1�Prishe...Do you think that the dragon you saw may be the same one portrayed in the painting of Al'Taieu?
1�Do you not remember the painting brought back by Grezzo from the Tenshodo?
1�I realize that back on the mainland, no one has the time to wonder about the fates of their lost brothers.
1�However, I pray that the powers that led you to Tavnazia turn out to be a blessing for both our peoples.
1�...By the way, where is the other traveler that arrived with you here in the safehold?
1�I wish to hear his tales of the mainland as well...
1�Prishe, Ulmia. Please come with me. There is something we must speak of.
1�Ah,  . Welcome back to the safehold.
1�This may sound odd, but on behalf of the residents of Tavnazia, I would like to thank you.
1�Were it not for your arrival on this island, we would have more than likely been trapped here until our deaths--our existence unknown to those back on the mainland.
1�And to think that I would be reunited once again with my granddaughter... There is nothing I could say or do that could express my gratitude.
1�Why, if it is not a messenger from the Far East. You must be exhausted from your long journey.
1�Welcome to our humble town. My name is Despachiaire, Ulmia's grandfather.
1�I see. So you wish to speak with Bahamut...
1�I apologize, but I must ask you to refrain from visiting the avatar at the moment.
1�Bahamut has built a nest but a few malms from this safehold. If anyone or anything were to disturb him, the results could be catastrophic for Tavnazia.
1�The diplomat from Jeuno, Nag'molada, should be returning from the Sacrarium shortly.
1�I request that you accompany him on his journey to Bahamut's lair.
1�Until then, feel free to rest within our city's walls. We shall try our best to meet any of your needs.
1�I apologize for her actions. While it may not show, Prishe is cursed by a terrible sickness.
1�I wish she would stay in the safehold and rest, but that personality of hers will not let her do so. I am amazed her body holds at all...
1�Now that Nag'molada has promised the revival of trade talks with Jeuno, Tavnazia needs Prishe to be healthy.
1�Nag'molada!Ulmia was only attempting to stop Prishe from doing something...unforgivable.
1�This traveler, Tenzen, is the true culprit. It was he who tricked my granddaughter into taking up this ridiculous journey.
1�She spoke with the abhorrent god of chaos! What more evidence do we need!?
1�It all makes sense now. Why else would Bahamut choose Tavnazia as his place of return!? It is all because of this girl!
1�She is the origin of all our troubles! Perhaps it is even her fault that the beastmen first converged on Tavnazia twenty years ago!
1�Save our nation? How am I to believe this after what I have seen?
1�If the Marquisate remained, the cathedral theologians would have discovered the true reason behind this child's existence and the terrible things she is planning.
1�Ah, forgive me, Altana.I should have revealed everything to Nag'molada. It was my mistake to conceal what I knew to protect our city's image.
1�He could have possibly led us to the truth about the true intentions of the abhorrent one...
1�And perhaps we should question the loyalty of Mildaurion C Giloumet as well? What were her true intentions?
1�I have recently heard rumors that the San d'Orian Cathedral is attempting to capture her!
1�This knight has been dispatched by order of the San d'Orian Cathedral to search out the missing Cardinal Mildaurion. He arrived here via a Duchy airship.
1�Well...If this is what the cathedral desires, I am not one to stand in its way...
1�You are working with Nag'molada...? I see...
1�So Ulmia truly left with Prishe...
1�Perhaps there was nothing that an old man such as myself could have done to prevent it...
1�I will not allow you to go tagging along with the abhorrent one! I will not allow it!
1�Ulmia!
1�I did everything I could to provide for my friends and family in this cursed place...
1�I never realized that my actions were only tying them down...
1� ...Is Ulmia... How is she doing?
1�Sir Louverance!

1�I can sleep easier knowing that such a noble knight as yourself is watching over my dear Ulmia. However, she is often one to hide her true feelings away from others, even though she may be in pain.
1�You... You are not causing her any pain, are you?
1�Wh-what!?
1�Exactly! There is no way she could know of the painting. She was only a mere child when the piece was donated to the cathedral. Oh, why must you blame yourself, poor Ulmia?
1�Sir Louverance! I know some of the history behind the painting. Let me tell you of what I know.
1�Long ago, I helped in the transport of the relic to the cathedral. Much tumult arose as a result of bringing that painting here.
1�Yes...It was some twenty-five years ago that the painting was brought to the archipelago.
1�According to the Marquisate officials, the painting was found deep within ancient ruins known as the Temple of Uggalepih.
1�It is said that the painting depicts a scene in the verse of a legendary song--the ancients and their attempt to open the Gates of Paradise...
1�Yes, I remember it like it was yesterday...A gate of light hovering over a grand city...The gatekeeper roaring to the heavens...
1�The gatekeeper took the shape of a mighty dragon. However, his four legs were bound by mighty shackles.
1�This image was the strongest in the painting. Many of the missionaries that came to view the painting would often call it the relic of chains, or the relic of the dragon.
1�Yes, until Cardinal Mildaurion viewed the painting. It was she who told us the city was Al'Taieu.
1�Though I may be mistaken, I seem to recall that before arriving in Tavnazia, Mildaurion was a priest who wandered the Outlands on a quest for spiritual enlightenment.

1�I have also heard tales that many of the holy relics that reached the archipelago were brought from the Outlands by thieves and pirates. Perhaps the cardinal obtained her knowledge of Al'Taieu in these forsaken areas.
1�Yes, I also remember how a group of Mithra came from those Outlands, demanding that we return the painting to the temple.
1�We were relieved, and with those Mithra beasts gone, we could go back to our normal, everyday lives.
1�I do not remember their names. I do not think they were ever referred to by anything other than the title of ??sin hunters.??
1�Sir Louverance.A young Mithran sin hunter visited the safehold a number of days ago.
1�If you can find her, she may be able to better inform you of the secrets behind the painting.

1�Atmacite is best described as the crystalline agglomeration of a creature's soul.Our scientists have succeeded in discovering a way to tap its power to serve the efforts of the Voidwatch.
1�By infusing one's body with atmacite, it is possible to obtain powers akin to those once possessed by the creature whence it came, rather like turning a beast's fangs upon its own kind.
1�At first glance, atmacite appears to be the perfect artificial enhancement. However, it does suffer from a single limitation: its power is unleashed only when engaged in a Voidwatch operation.
1�Research to identify the exact reason for this continues, but most scientists find the spectral alignment theory compelling.
1�That is, being formed of Voidwalker souls, atmacite will surge to life only when its bearer is existentially aligned to its dimension of origin.
1�From this it can be inferred that Voidwalkers are stripped of considerable strength when they cross over into Vana'diel.
1�But I suspect this is of little interest to a layman like you. Allow me to return to the subject at hand.
1�The infusion of atmacite requires cruor, a potent energy source that takes the form of shiny red granules.
1�Cruor is obtainable by various means, felling a Voidwalker being the most common of all.As you can never have too much cruor, I urge you to be diligent in its procurement.
1�We've recently perfected a method for improving atmacite potency. The process is called enrichment, and involves fusing cruor on to atmacite to amplify its power.

1�Atmacite can be enriched in stages up to a maximum of level 
�. The quantity of cruor required varies with the variety of atmacite as well as its current enrichment level.

1�Under normal conditions, atmacite enrichment is an intensive process that demands trained hands.For reasons yet to be determined, however, both infusion and enrichment can be safely performed by laymen, provided they're at a planar rift.
1�Keep this in mind should the need arise to reconfigure your atmacite with haste.
